Abraham Jacobus Visagie impersonated a senior prosecutor at the Springbok Magistrate s Court in December 2015.He approached a woman who faced charges of culpable homicide. According to a statement by police he ''promised to protect her against prosecution''.But he wanted R6 000 and R15 000 for his ''associate''.The incident was reported to the Hawks."He first appeared in Court on Monday 13 June 2016 and was granted R2000 bail. On 12 December 2016 he pleaded guilty and consequently the Springbok Magistrate's Court sentenced him to three years imprisonment wholly suspended for three years on condition that he is not found guilty of similar offences '' police said in a statement. TMG Digital/Sunday Times